			    STPJS 321</div>
  <div class="topic">Covenants of the Fathers Revealed</div>
  <p class="std">Who is there that would not give all his goods to feed the poor,<span class="footRef">1</span> and pour out his gold and silver
  to the four winds,<span class="footRef">2</span> to go where Judge Higbee has gone?</p>
  <p class="std">That which hath been hid from before the foundation of the world<span class="footRef">3</span> is revealed to babes and
  sucklings<span class="footRef">4</span> in the last days.</p>
  <p class="std">The world is reserved unto burning<span class="footRef">5</span> in the last days. He shall send Elijah the prophet, and he
  shall reveal the covenants of the fathers in relation to the children, and the covenants of the children
  in relation to the fathers.<span class="footRef">6</span></p>
  <p class="std">Four destroying angels<span class="footRef">7</span> holding power over the four quarters of the earth<span class="footRef">8</span> until the servants of
  God<span class="footRef">9</span> are sealed in their foreheads,<span class="footRef">10</span> which signifies sealing the blessing<span class="footRef">11</span> upon their heads, meaning
  the everlasting covenant,<span class="footRef">12</span> thereby making their calling and election sure.<span class="footRef">13</span> When a seal is put upon
  the father and mother, it secures their posterity, so that they cannot be lost, but will be saved by
  virtue of the covenant of their father and mother.<span class="footRef">14</span></p>
  <p class="std">To the mourners I would say&mdash;Do as the husband and the father would instruct you, and you
  shall be reunited.</p>
  <p class="std">The speaker continued to teach the doctrine of election<span class="footRef">15</span> and the sealing powers<span class="footRef">16</span> and
  principles, and spoke of the doctrine of election with the seed of Abraham,<span class="footRef">17</span> and the sealing of
  blessings upon his posterity, and the sealing of the fathers and children,<span class="footRef">18</span> according to the
  declarations of the prophets. He then spoke of Judge Higbee in the world of spirits,<span class="footRef">19</span> and the
  blessings which he would obtain, and of the kind spirit and disposition of Judge Higbee while living;
  none of which was reported. (Aug. 13, 1843.) DHC 5:529–531.</p>
  <div class="topic">The Priesthood</div>
  <p class="std">President Smith read the 7th Chap. Hebrews<span class="footRef">20</span> and said: Salem<span class="footRef">21</span> is designed for a Hebrew term.
  It should be Shiloam, which signifies righteousness and peace; as it is, it is nothing&mdash;neither
  Hebrew, Greek, Latin, French, nor any other language.</p>
  <p class="std">I say to all those who are disposed to set up stakes for the Almighty, You will come short of the
  glory of God.<span class="footRef">22</span></p>
  <p class="std">To become a joint heir<span class="footRef">23</span> of the heirship of the Son, one must put away<span class="footRef">24</span> all his false traditions.<span class="footRef">25</span></p>
